# Drop polyfills for old browsers. Default Next.js browserslist includes
# browsers that don't support Array.prototype.at / .flat / .flatMap /
# Object.fromEntries / Object.hasOwn / String.prototype.trimEnd — so Babel
# ships polyfills for all of them. Lighthouse flagged 11 KiB of these.
#
# Anna's audience is on modern phones / laptops / tablets. Anyone on a
# browser older than ~2022 is a vanishing minority for a wellness site.
# This config drops the polyfills + cuts main-thread script time.
#
# Coverage check: this config still covers ~95%+ of global traffic
# (Chrome 90+, Firefox 90+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+ all support the features
# we use). Run `npx browserslist` from web/ to see exact browser list.
last 2 years
not dead
not op_mini all
not ie 11
